# Vocabulary Rule (DP-1)

This rule governs naming only.

## 1) Canonical domain nouns
Only these are first-class domain objects:
- `Channel`
- `Playlist`
- `Work`

`Play` is an action, not a persisted entity.

## 2) Hard lock for exhibition terms
- `Exhibition`, `Season`, and `Program` are playlist roles/UI chrome only.
- Never introduce them as new domain entities/tables.
- Represent via `playlistRole` metadata on `Playlist` or UI-only state.

## 3) Naming consistency
- IDs: `channelId`, `playlistId`, `workId`.
- Collections: `channels`, `playlists`, `works`.
- File names: `snake_case.dart`.
- Types/enums: `PascalCase`.
- Methods/variables: `camelCase`.
- Booleans: predicate-style (`is*`, `has*`, `can*`, `should*`).

## 4) Forbidden domain synonyms in identifiers
Do not use these as domain nouns:
- `artwork` (use `work`)
- `show`, `season`, `program` (use playlist + role)
- `feed` (use `channel`)

## 5) Personal collection modeling
- "My Collection" is a pinned `Channel`.
- Do not create separate `Collection` domain entities.
